  "abstract": {
    "value": "An electroreductive cross-coupling of prop-2-yn-1-yl acetates with chloro(vinyl)silanes for producing tetrasubstituted silylallenes is developed. The method enables the formation of a new C-Si bond through cathodic reduction to form the silyl radical, radical addition across the C≡C bond, alkenyl anion intermediate formation, and deacetoxylation, and represents a mild, practical route to the synthesis of silylallenes. Mechanistic studies reveal that CoCl2 acts as the mediator to promote the formation of the alkenyl anion intermediate via electron transfer.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
    "confidence": 0.98,
    "human_checked": false
  },
